All Classes

Class Description
Edge
This class establishes a link (aka an edge) between every pair of node, this link is an object that in the graph will be attached to the parent Node, considering this, the edge object contains the Node of the Child and the weight of the edge.
FileSet
Receives the file and decomposes them line by line, sending it to the correct place.
Graph
The Graph class builds the entire graph, which means it contains all the information regarding all the Nodes and the Edges between them.
Instance
Instance of a file, to be used in a Linked List containing all Instances.
LL_model
Computes weight of the edge using the Log-Likelihood (LL) Method
Main
This class calls every other class by the correct order, receives the inputs from the users, and prints the correct outcome.
MDL_model
Computes weight of the edge using the Minimum Description Length (MDL) Method
NaiveBayesClassifier
In the NaiveBayesClassifier class we go through each Instance of the Test File and compute the joint probability P_B.
Node
Object that stores the information about each Feature of the Train Set.
ScoreModel
Interface, it's incomplete and general and therefore needs to be implemented and overwritten by actual score models
TestSet
This class extends the FileSet class so it opens and correctly divides the Test File.
TrainSet
This class extends the FileSet class so it opens and correctly divides the Train File.
Tree
This Class extends the Graph, this happens because a tree is a type of graph but minimally connected.
